{{champion:145}} 
She remind me of Tarzan, she is disconnected from the social world. She feel very instinct driven if you are an enemy she will attack, you if you are a friend she will protect. 

Also I just love her interaction with the honey fruit.

{{champion:50}} 
Because he's a pragmatic tactical mastermind who makes the decisions no one else wants to; a man who claims the right to rule with his own hands, yet divides it amongst himself and his equals; a man who places his faith in the power of the country rather than the power of the individual; a man who has wrestled a demon for its secrets - and won.

{{champion:60}} 
Because she's a black-hearted predator - the very embodiment of emptiness: a completely selfish, insatiable creature that has long since lost all of its humanity, and is now consumed by its obsession with - and hunger for - eternal youth; a woman who knows and understands that what she does is considered "wrong", but does it anyway; a master manipulator, who lures the innocent and guilty alike into her web only to be slain; a woman whose beauty, intelligence and charisma only accentuate the ravenous monster lurking beneath.

{{champion:82}} 
Because he's a ruthless tyrant whose desire to dominate all living - and dead - things drives him past the realm of death, rising from defeat again and again out of pure malice and the strength of his dark will; because he laughs at his enemies even as they strike him down; because the Black Mist has no control over him - he controls it; because a thousand kingdoms may rise and fall, burned to ashes or reduced to shadows and dust, but Mordekaiser always remains.

{{champion:161}} 
Because he's a wholly alien entity whose hunger for knowledge only grows with every new piece of information he acquires; an entity whose scientific curiosity about the worlds he finds himself in is matched only by the cold, clinical detachment he analyzes his test subjects with; an entity who knows the cosmic truths of the universe, and warps reality through the forbidden power of the Void; an entity who has glimpsed the ultimate knowledge - and will have it.

{{champion:85}} 

He reminds me of me, that's all I'm saying.

{{champion:53}} 

That robot song from Spongebob, not just that radio one, but "WHEN WORLDS COLLIDE..."

{{champion:161}} 

He's not my most favorite but hearing his nonsense about testing and whatnot reminds me a mix of GLaDOS and C'Thun from World of Warcraft.

{{champion:203}} 

Because everyone wants a friend 'till the end.

I'm also an identical twin, so ... kinda relatable that they were the same and split into two. The same but clearly different with their own identities. Not trying to be philosophical, but it's pretty relatable. Also I like the whole Dark & Light aspect, as well that Death isn't always painful it can be quick and merciful. This is why I call them the Duality of Death instead of the Eternal Hunters.
